00:38.186 --> 00:40.177
[Woman singing]

01:28.970 --> 01:30.961
[Thunder]

02:18.987 --> 02:20.477
[Squeaks]

02:38.373 --> 02:40.034
[Bell chimes]

02:43.044 --> 02:44.705
[Bell chimes]

02:47.649 --> 02:48.980
[Bell chimes]

02:50.118 --> 02:51.244
[Horse nickers]

02:52.320 --> 02:53.651
[Bell chimes]

03:14.409 --> 03:16.400
[Man talking indistinctly]

03:20.949 --> 03:22.439
SIMON: Granted, the craftsmanship's...

03:22.484 --> 03:24.111
not on a par with the Italians...

03:24.152 --> 03:27.485
but for Eastern Europe, it's not bad.

03:29.991 --> 03:32.255
He assures me it's 14th Century...

03:32.293 --> 03:35.353
but these materials, maybe early 15th.

03:35.396 --> 03:37.191
The guy wanted 10,000 for it...

03:37.324 --> 03:38.518
till he found out who was buying.

03:38.559 --> 03:41.619
Then he said Mr. Van Helsing's always been his best customer.

03:41.662 --> 03:44.130
Don't worry. You paid five.

03:46.100 --> 03:48.330
VAN HELSING: Did you translate the markings?

03:48.369 --> 03:51.702
It's a Slav dialect. "All fear he who walks...

03:51.739 --> 03:54.037
"beneath the crown of eternal night."

03:54.074 --> 03:56.065
No, no, no. It's not crown.

03:56.110 --> 03:57.702
It's halo.

03:57.745 --> 04:00.714
"Beneath the halo of eternal night."

04:00.748 --> 04:01.737
SIMON: Oh, well.

04:01.782 --> 04:04.012
You see why the design never survived.

04:04.051 --> 04:05.382
And look how heavy it is compared...

04:05.419 --> 04:06.977
to what they were using in England at the time.

04:07.021 --> 04:10.582
Well, the English made them for firing arrow shafts of wood.

04:10.624 --> 04:14.685
This was made for firing metal-- silver.

04:14.728 --> 04:15.854
[Chuckles]

04:15.896 --> 04:17.692
It sounds like something your grandfather...

04:17.731 --> 04:19.596
would've used to hunt the old...

04:19.632 --> 04:20.622
VAN HELSING: Simon!

04:20.668 --> 04:23.136
You know how I dislike this kind of talk.

04:23.170 --> 04:24.330
Sorry.

04:24.371 --> 04:25.668
VAN HELSING: How my poor grandfather...

04:25.706 --> 04:29.403
could have inspired a character out of Bram Stoker's book...

04:29.443 --> 04:30.740
I'll never know.

04:30.778 --> 04:33.076
In truth, he was simply a country doctor...

04:33.113 --> 04:34.740
VAN HELSING: who built up an antique business.

04:34.782 --> 04:36.079
Nothing more.

04:36.116 --> 04:38.607
SIMON: So, what should we say in terms of resale value?

04:38.652 --> 04:41.348
I am not interested in the resale.

04:41.388 --> 04:42.650
VAN HELSING: I want it for my collection.

04:42.690 --> 04:43.748
Another one.

04:43.791 --> 04:47.158
We turn a profit, do we not?

04:47.194 --> 04:49.185
I will keep what I wish.

04:49.230 --> 04:50.219
[Knock on door]

04:50.264 --> 04:51.424
[Door opens]

04:52.466 --> 04:55.026
Mr. Van Helsing, last of the manifests.

04:55.069 --> 04:56.195
SOLINA: Will you be needing anything?

04:56.237 --> 04:57.761
No, no, no. You go.

04:57.805 --> 04:59.500
OK. Good night, then.

04:59.540 --> 05:00.871
Good night, Simon.

05:04.578 --> 05:05.704
[Door closes]

05:08.249 --> 05:10.717
Picture this. We walk to Waterloo Station.

05:10.751 --> 05:12.719
We board the next train, and three hours later...

05:12.753 --> 05:14.550
we're in Paris for the weekend.

05:14.588 --> 05:15.577
[Sighs]

05:16.924 --> 05:20.052
Does English charm work on English women?

05:20.094 --> 05:22.062
Why not, Solina? One reason.

05:22.096 --> 05:25.259
I don't date men that I work with.

05:25.299 --> 05:28.063
Where was that rule a month ago?

05:28.102 --> 05:29.592
It's new.

05:42.616 --> 05:44.607
[Train rumbling]

06:01.569 --> 06:03.036
[Doorbell buzzes]

06:03.070 --> 06:04.537
[Buzz]

06:04.572 --> 06:06.039
[Door clicks open]

06:08.242 --> 06:09.368
Good evening.

06:09.410 --> 06:12.106
I heard you had some sort of security problem.

06:12.146 --> 06:13.374
No, sir.

06:13.414 --> 06:14.381
You do now.

06:14.415 --> 06:15.404
[Crackles]

06:19.653 --> 06:20.642
Aah!

06:22.690 --> 06:23.657
TRICK: Nice shot.

06:23.691 --> 06:25.556
Move, move, move.

06:25.593 --> 06:27.083
Move and think.

06:33.934 --> 06:34.958
[Beeps]

06:35.970 --> 06:36.959
[Beeps]

06:47.481 --> 06:48.470
[Beeps]

06:48.515 --> 06:50.005
[Grunts]

06:50.050 --> 06:51.813
Come on.

06:59.793 --> 07:01.351
[Beeping]

07:01.395 --> 07:03.329
Pass code decrypted.

07:03.364 --> 07:05.161
TRICK: Accessing.

07:15.109 --> 07:16.736
TRICK: Security shutting down.

07:16.777 --> 07:18.005
[Machinery humming]

07:20.914 --> 07:22.347
[Beeping]

07:32.826 --> 07:33.952
[Machinery clangs]

07:39.900 --> 07:41.731
[Classical music plays]

08:02.423 --> 08:05.187
COMPUTER: Fingerprint identification confirmed.

08:05.225 --> 08:07.250
Stand by for voice recognition.

08:07.294 --> 08:08.522
[Click]

08:08.562 --> 08:09.995
TAPE: Matthew Van Helsing.

08:10.030 --> 08:12.658
COMPUTER: Voice recognition confirmed.

08:12.700 --> 08:15.134
Standby for retinal scan.

08:19.006 --> 08:20.997
[Beeping and clicking]

08:57.711 --> 08:59.679
EDDIE: This--is this it?

08:59.713 --> 09:01.374
MARCUS: Garage sale. Leave it.

09:34.681 --> 09:35.875
Hello?

09:49.429 --> 09:51.090
[Solina gasps]

10:04.111 --> 10:05.840
[Gasps] Ohh.

10:05.879 --> 10:07.073
[Panting]

10:09.283 --> 10:10.375
Hello, precious.

10:10.417 --> 10:13.409
Marcus, you idiot.

10:15.122 --> 10:16.851
Question for you.

10:16.890 --> 10:19.791
Are we supposed to make profit off of this?

10:20.894 --> 10:22.191
Shh!

10:22.229 --> 10:23.389
[Sighs]

10:23.430 --> 10:24.727
What have they found?

10:24.765 --> 10:26.392
Furniture, candlesticks...

10:26.433 --> 10:28.264
some old piece-of-shit pottery.

10:28.302 --> 10:29.394
I gotta tell you, babe.

10:29.436 --> 10:31.336
This is one morbid old bastard you work for.

10:31.371 --> 10:33.862
What about artwork or diamonds or gold?

10:33.907 --> 10:36.467
Fucking crucifixes and coffee cups.

10:36.510 --> 10:41.641
You don't build this kind of security...

10:41.682 --> 10:43.616
without a gold mine to hide.

10:43.650 --> 10:45.447
Listen to me.

10:45.485 --> 10:48.477
You and I are going to find it.

10:51.325 --> 10:52.815
Trust me.

11:09.536 --> 11:11.231
[Screeches]

11:39.032 --> 11:40.294
[Footsteps]

11:40.334 --> 11:42.234
MAN: Jesus Christ.

11:43.470 --> 11:45.597
All the tunnels line up.

11:45.639 --> 11:46.936
The main vault should be behind this door.

11:46.974 --> 11:50.273
NIGHTSHADE: Hey, Marcus. What's with all the voodoo?

11:50.310 --> 11:52.676
EDDIE: You really sure we want to do do this?

11:52.713 --> 11:55.443
If it's worth locking, it's worth taking.

11:55.482 --> 11:57.507
Breach it.

12:11.798 --> 12:13.129
[Grunts]

12:36.924 --> 12:40.917
What...the hell is that?

12:42.930 --> 12:43.954
TRICK: She said money.

12:43.997 --> 12:45.123
She said gold!

12:45.165 --> 12:47.463
I said he guarded it like gold.

12:47.501 --> 12:49.196
I said I didn't know why.

12:49.236 --> 12:51.568
Fucking thousand-year-old silverware?

12:52.940 --> 12:55.704
EDDIE: Probably got his goddamn mother in that thing.

12:55.742 --> 12:56.800
TRICK: Marcus?

12:57.878 --> 12:59.140
Marcus!

12:59.179 --> 13:00.669
DAX: This is bullshit, man.

13:00.714 --> 13:03.012
We're here for money, Marcus!

13:03.050 --> 13:05.416
The skulls are to scare us.

13:05.452 --> 13:07.943
The crosses, the coffin, all of it.

13:07.988 --> 13:11.151
It's a grand-spanking mind fuck to scare off thieves.

13:11.191 --> 13:13.955
MARCUS: If you make a killing, why hide it in a safe...

13:13.994 --> 13:16.087
SOLINA: When you can hide it in a coffin?

13:16.129 --> 13:19.860
MARCUS: This look like an old wood box to you guys?

13:19.900 --> 13:21.925
The Holy Grail, the Golden Fleece...

13:21.969 --> 13:25.871
the crown-fucking jewels, whatever it is, it's inside.

13:25.906 --> 13:27.168
MARCUS: Eddie, Dax, and Shade...

13:27.207 --> 13:29.903
you get your gear and get this thing open.

13:31.011 --> 13:33.707
No, I am not touching that fucking coffin.

13:33.747 --> 13:35.180
You want to get paid?

13:35.215 --> 13:36.341
Get it open!

13:37.784 --> 13:38.773
[Crowbar clangs]

13:40.053 --> 13:42.851
EDDIE: Wasn't part of the frickin' plan.

13:42.889 --> 13:44.288
There's no latches here. There's no locks.

13:44.324 --> 13:46.451
Yeah, well, it's gotta open somehow.

13:47.995 --> 13:48.962
EDDIE: Whoa, whoa, whoa.

13:48.996 --> 13:51.021
I got a seam here.

13:57.337 --> 13:58.565
Aah!

13:58.605 --> 13:59.936
[Gurgling]

13:59.973 --> 14:00.962
Jesus Christ!

14:02.676 --> 14:03.938
Get down!

14:05.612 --> 14:06.738
[Gasps]

14:09.916 --> 14:11.816
Fuck.

14:11.852 --> 14:13.843
[Alarm ringing]

14:21.762 --> 14:23.354
It's not possible.

14:35.542 --> 14:37.840
Find us a goddamn hole and blow it!

14:37.878 --> 14:39.106
This wall.

14:39.146 --> 14:40.477
I am not touching anything.

14:40.514 --> 14:42.778
You will do exactly what he tells you to do!

14:46.987 --> 14:48.750
NIGHTSHADE: Give me a hand with this.

14:48.789 --> 14:51.314
- Find some spots.
- Right.

15:04.538 --> 15:06.768
MARCUS: Why do you build this?

15:07.908 --> 15:09.307
All right, you guys. Get down.

15:15.415 --> 15:17.007
One, two...

15:26.059 --> 15:28.357
It's clear. Come on.

15:28.395 --> 15:29.362
TRICK: Yeah!

15:29.396 --> 15:30.363
Whoo!

15:30.397 --> 15:32.160
All right. Make a right.

15:32.199 --> 15:34.133
Take another right to the river...

15:34.167 --> 15:35.293
and then we're out.

15:35.335 --> 15:36.962
[Grunts]

15:37.003 --> 15:39.471
Hey, guys. The coffin.

15:39.506 --> 15:40.905
What are you looking at? Help me!

15:40.941 --> 15:42.704
Help yourself. Come on, let's go!

15:44.177 --> 15:45.838
SOLINA: Gentlemen...

15:45.879 --> 15:49.508
we are not leaving without the prize.

16:13.907 --> 16:15.898
[Water trickling]

16:17.077 --> 16:19.700
God help us all.

16:20.200 --> 16:21.758
[Panting]

16:21.802 --> 16:23.167
[Growling]

16:31.745 --> 16:33.736
[Panting]

16:48.329 --> 16:49.660
[Sniffs]

16:51.065 --> 16:52.293
[Sighs]

16:53.300 --> 16:54.426
[Knock on door]

16:54.468 --> 16:56.299
LUCY: Hey, Mare. Rise and shine.

17:01.809 --> 17:03.003
[Sighs]

17:10.617 --> 17:11.742
Here's your coffee.

17:11.785 --> 17:13.945
We're gonna be late.

17:13.988 --> 17:15.527
[Whispering] Whatever.

17:24.136 --> 17:26.934
MARY: I've decided. I just won't let it get to me.

17:26.972 --> 17:28.098
LUCY: So, what do you think it is?

17:28.140 --> 17:29.266
You tell me.

17:29.307 --> 17:31.935
Your dot-com dream analyst says I'm having a baby.

17:31.977 --> 17:34.378
Father Devereaux says I should go back to Xanax...

17:34.511 --> 17:36.001
and your bartender friend Ray...

17:36.046 --> 17:38.537
Ha! He insists I'm just repressed.

17:39.717 --> 17:40.706
Ooh.

17:41.719 --> 17:43.687
- Mm-hmm.
- What?

17:43.721 --> 17:44.710
Nothing.

17:45.889 --> 17:47.686
I just keep thinking, Mary, that maybe...

17:47.725 --> 17:48.919
if you had a man in your bed, you might not--

17:48.959 --> 17:51.359
I wouldn't need the man in my head. Thanks.

18:14.251 --> 18:15.240
[Beeps]

18:21.925 --> 18:24.223
Where are the guards? What happened?

18:24.261 --> 18:26.229
We were robbed, Simon.

18:26.263 --> 18:29.061
We were robbed. I told you.

18:29.099 --> 18:30.396
SIMON: But downstairs, it's all there.

18:30.434 --> 18:31.401
What did they take?

18:31.435 --> 18:33.300
VAN HELSING: My private holdings.

18:33.337 --> 18:34.599
SIMON: The abbey.

18:34.638 --> 18:38.472
Yes. My artifacts, textiles, everything that I call my own.

18:38.509 --> 18:40.238
Where are the police? Why aren't they all over?

18:40.277 --> 18:41.539
There's no need to inform the police.

18:41.578 --> 18:42.875
The guards were not hurt.

18:42.913 --> 18:45.814
I compensated them well. They understand my wishes.

18:45.849 --> 18:47.111
I don't understand your wishes.

18:47.151 --> 18:48.550
No police!

18:53.223 --> 18:54.952
Simon, look.

18:54.992 --> 18:57.392
VAN HELSING: Some of my holdings were acquired...

18:57.428 --> 19:02.593
in a manner not quite befitting the scrutiny of the law.

19:05.035 --> 19:07.503
You understand what I mean, huh?

19:09.473 --> 19:10.940
Where are you going?

19:11.975 --> 19:14.375
Well, I must tend to this matter myself.

19:14.411 --> 19:19.007
And in my absence, I will need you to run the business.

19:19.049 --> 19:20.539
Matthew, what did they take?

19:22.019 --> 19:23.486
Matthew.

19:27.291 --> 19:28.656
Confide in me.

19:28.692 --> 19:29.784
[Van Helsing sighs]

19:29.827 --> 19:32.261
You've always trusted me before.

19:32.296 --> 19:37.290
Christ, you've been like a--a father to me.

19:37.334 --> 19:39.199
A father? Ha ha.

19:41.071 --> 19:42.732
No, Simon.

19:44.875 --> 19:47.673
That is something I was never meant to be.

20:04.428 --> 20:06.123
MARCUS: So, how long to the Caymans?

20:06.163 --> 20:07.357
CHARLIE: We're under an hour.

20:07.397 --> 20:08.386
[Click]

20:10.067 --> 20:11.932
God damn it!

20:11.969 --> 20:13.937
[Panting]

20:13.971 --> 20:14.938
Look, I told you.

20:14.972 --> 20:17.270
This thing is completely sealed.

20:17.307 --> 20:19.172
We'll have to blow it like a goddamn safe.

20:19.209 --> 20:22.144
No, we are not using explosives.

20:22.179 --> 20:24.044
I mean, he put stuff in.

20:24.081 --> 20:25.810
He takes stuff out.

20:25.849 --> 20:27.578
Just solve it.

20:29.653 --> 20:30.881
You heard the lady.

20:30.921 --> 20:32.388
Just solve it.

20:34.291 --> 20:35.280
[Door closes]

20:36.994 --> 20:38.962
TRICK: Dax and Eddie get impaled.

20:38.996 --> 20:40.395
What the hell is going on?

20:40.430 --> 20:43.365
- You know something.
- Would you just go sit down?

20:43.400 --> 20:44.594
Just sit down.

20:48.772 --> 20:49.761
Ow!

20:54.244 --> 20:55.233
Uhh.

20:58.015 --> 20:59.039
[Grunts]

21:02.085 --> 21:04.315
There was probably cash upstairs!

21:05.856 --> 21:08.416
We didn't bother looking. Un-fucking-believable.

21:09.793 --> 21:11.624
Always doing what she says.

21:11.662 --> 21:15.223
God! Poor boys doing what she says.

21:17.034 --> 21:19.468
[Mocking] We're not leaving without the prize.

21:19.503 --> 21:20.834
[Sighs]

21:44.928 --> 21:47.158
[Panting]

21:57.174 --> 21:58.266
Ooh!

22:20.831 --> 22:21.798
[Sniffs]

22:21.832 --> 22:23.959
[Coughs] Ohh.

22:31.675 --> 22:33.870
NIGHTSHADE: What? Oh, man.

22:34.978 --> 22:37.378
What are those, leeches?

22:39.650 --> 22:42.118
Still juice in this thing?

22:47.925 --> 22:49.153
Oh, my G--

22:53.196 --> 22:55.164
Aah! Aah!

22:55.198 --> 22:56.187
Aah!

22:58.635 --> 22:59.659
[Grunts]

22:59.703 --> 23:01.034
[Panting]

23:02.105 --> 23:03.094
Aah!

23:07.811 --> 23:09.642
[Grunting]

23:10.847 --> 23:12.075
God damn it!

23:14.685 --> 23:16.846
God damn it!

23:16.887 --> 23:19.856
Uhh! Uhh!

23:23.660 --> 23:25.252
[Groans]

23:32.769 --> 23:33.895
[Grunts]

24:27.018 --> 24:28.349
NIGHTSHADE: Rubies.

24:41.800 --> 24:43.734
Aah!

24:46.638 --> 24:47.935
[Hisses]

24:50.175 --> 24:52.166
[Nightshade screaming]

25:05.490 --> 25:06.821
Shade?

25:10.462 --> 25:13.124
Shade, quit fucking around. Get out here now.

25:20.839 --> 25:22.636
[Metal creaking]

25:22.674 --> 25:25.108
[Door bangs]

25:25.143 --> 25:26.735
Shade, you back there?

25:26.778 --> 25:28.109
[Door bangs]

25:42.127 --> 25:44.152
I do not need this shit.

25:44.195 --> 25:45.457
Unh!

25:45.497 --> 25:47.124
[Gasps]

25:47.165 --> 25:48.359
TRICK: The fuck?

25:57.575 --> 25:58.599
[Banging]

26:43.188 --> 26:44.382
[Growls]

26:45.423 --> 26:46.651
[Grunting]

26:48.226 --> 26:50.217
SOLINA: What the hell was that?

26:50.261 --> 26:52.092
It was probably just turbulence.

26:53.965 --> 26:54.954
[Gasps]

26:54.999 --> 26:56.489
Trick?

27:02.941 --> 27:04.875
What the hell are you?

27:04.909 --> 27:06.740
[Breathes deeply]

27:14.452 --> 27:15.419
[Gasps]

27:15.453 --> 27:17.080
Oh, my God.

27:19.891 --> 27:22.189
Solina?

27:22.227 --> 27:24.320
Solina? Solina?

27:26.965 --> 27:28.865
MARCUS: Solina, what are you doing?!

27:30.635 --> 27:32.398
[Growls]

27:32.437 --> 27:34.462
MARCUS: Get your hands off of her!

27:34.506 --> 27:35.734
Get off of her!

27:40.912 --> 27:43.312
[Grunting]

27:48.286 --> 27:50.311
[Grunts]

27:50.355 --> 27:52.289
You're not from that coffin.

27:52.323 --> 27:53.381
[Grunts]

28:01.599 --> 28:03.157
You're not from that coffin!

28:03.201 --> 28:04.566
[Marcus panting]

28:06.404 --> 28:07.393
Aargh!

28:08.506 --> 28:10.201
What the hell are you doing?!

28:18.183 --> 28:19.172
Marcus?

28:28.860 --> 28:30.691
[Thunder]

28:30.728 --> 28:31.752
Uhh.

28:32.797 --> 28:34.594
[Thunder]

28:34.632 --> 28:36.259
Charlie!

28:38.303 --> 28:39.964
Stay in the light!

28:40.004 --> 28:41.938
[Screaming]

28:58.423 --> 29:00.448
[Thunder]

29:15.740 --> 29:17.401
Wake up.

29:20.945 --> 29:22.276
Wake up.

29:25.350 --> 29:27.181
[Gasps]

29:27.218 --> 29:28.242
Wake up.

29:28.286 --> 29:30.516
MARY: Wake up.

29:30.555 --> 29:32.386
It's the dream.

29:34.058 --> 29:35.650
You know it's the dream.

29:35.693 --> 29:36.682
Wake up.

29:41.766 --> 29:43.893
[Shivering]

29:47.505 --> 29:49.166
[Sniffs]

29:54.012 --> 29:55.604
[Whispering] Mary.

29:56.914 --> 29:59.246
You are real.

30:05.923 --> 30:07.515
LUCY: Mary?

30:10.828 --> 30:14.059
Mary, wake up. Mary, wake up!

30:15.066 --> 30:16.761
You were screaming.

30:16.801 --> 30:18.769
God, you scared me!

30:18.803 --> 30:20.134
I saw him.

30:21.139 --> 30:22.766
I--I saw his face.

30:22.807 --> 30:24.865
Who?

30:27.101 --> 30:28.728
[Panting] Mary.

30:28.769 --> 30:31.101
There's something wrong with me, Lucy.

30:32.773 --> 30:34.866
There's something so wrong.

30:34.908 --> 30:36.398
[Crying]

30:37.744 --> 30:39.712
It's OK.

30:39.746 --> 30:41.873
